76561198026766250,Recommended,210950,18109631,"Posted: 19 September, 2015",all,Rubik,"Rune Classic includes the original Rune and the Halls of Valhalla expansion.  Gameplay is very similar to the original; however, there are a few noticeable changes.- In the single player campaign, many of the levels have been shortened and some have been removed completely.  This does help keep the game moving along (especially in the first cavern areas); though, fans of the original game will likely notice a few memorable areas missing.- A few new enemies have been added: skeletons, hellhounds, and frost giants.- Some of the weapon rune powers have been swapped.  For example, the viking short sword now has the vampire rune power, and the viking broad sword now has the befriend rune power.Overall, I still like the game.  The only complaint I have is that a couple bugs have not yet been fixed (as of version 1.10).- In the cave area just after Ragnar gets off the large beetle, there is a cliff area that will kill Ragnar if any items (weapons, shields, body parts, etc.) fall into it.- Near the end of the game, there is a cinema scene where the sarks are breaking through a wall with hammers.  This scene causes the game to crash unless you turn the volume down to zero in the game control panel."
